summary: This script checks if the argument count is less than or equal to 1. If true, it outputs "no argument" and exits with status 1. Else, it outputs "good" and exits with status 0.

details.comment: This script checks if the argument count is less than or equal to 1. If true, it outputs "no argument" and exits with status 1. Else, it outputs "good" and exits with status 0.
details.content:
#!/bin/bash
c0=$(echo $1 |wc -c )
#echo $c0
if [ $c0 -le 1 ]
then
	echo "no argument."
	exit 1
else
	echo "good"
	exit 0
fi
